post_text: For the 20/21 baseball season we will only have the 7th and 8th grade students participating. With the guidelines placed upon us as a district we are fortunate that we are able to play baseball this fall. We will be limited to only conference games (there will be no State Tournament this year) which also limits the amount of playing time for all students involved. Next year we are hopeful that 6th grade students will be able to participate for a State Championship. Thank you for your continuous support through these unprecedented times. Go Mustangs!

post_text: Mr. Tim Harms has resigned after 17 years serving as a board member of the Prairieview District #192 (April 2003-June 2006) and the Prairieview-Ogden District 197 (July 2006-June 2020). His dedication and leadership on the Board of Education will be missed. Thank you Tim!

Ogden Rose Public Library
June 6 at 9:38 AM ·

Hello, Ogden!

Starting on Tuesday June 9th Ogden Rose Library will begin their reopening procedures. Starting on that day at 11:00, we will be offering curbside pick up for any library materials you would like to check out or drop off. At this time, the inter-library loan program is temporarily unavailable so we are restricted to books, dvd's, and periodicals that are currently on our shelves. You can use this link to browse, check availabilty, and order. You will need your library card number. If you have any questions or require assistance in ordering materials, please email the library at roselibrary@comcast.net or call 217-582-2411.

We can't wait to see you!!

Reminder: Today is the 8th grade Graduation parade. Hope to see you in the parade or standing outside cheering them on.

We will have a 8th grade graduation parade on Tuesday, May 19 to honor the PVO Class of 2020. We will meet at the Royal Community Building on Tuesday, May 19 at 5:45 pm. We will Parade through Royal starting at 6. Then we will head to Ogden. We will have Fire truck(s) and a school bus leading the way. Please show your support by being outside waving or join the parade. Pass the word!

The 8th graders will receive their “Fathead” to keep before the parade!

Once a Mustang always a Mustang!

post_text:
Hi PVO
The weather is getting nicer out and I hope you are getting some fresh air but practicing your six foot social distancing! What I would like you to do is take a picture/short video of something you have done together as a family and post it to our Facebook/Twitter account. Examples: An Art project, cooking project, STEM project, playing games, etc.
Today, Mr. Fiscus (now Tuscola principal) ask his students to post a Dunking video (rim at whatever height). So start posting/sharing your positive picture/video with a description. I look forward to seeing all the pictures/videos. Thanks Mr. White

Update - Unfortunately Facebook only allows administrators to post videos/pictures in the comments on pages. Please email your pictures/videos to Mr White at vwhite@pvo.k12.il.us or Ms Lisa at alsipl@pvo.k12.il.us and we will be posting them.

post_text:
Hi PVO
During the school shut down bc of the Coronavirus/Covid-19 we will be providing FREE “Grab and Go Sack Lunches” to any PVO student that wants one starting Monday, March 23. The Pick up time will be from 10-11 a.m each day at all three buildings (Monday through Friday).

So all you need to do email the cook/school you want to pick the meal up at (see below) and provide your name, and student (s) name by Thursday at 10a.m. so we can order food. You can pick which building is closest to your home/babysitter not necessarily where your child(ren) go to school.

Menu for next week is Ham and cheese sandwich ,carrot sticks, chips, fruit cup, and milk.

For South Elementary-please email Susan at rosss@pvo.k12.il.us.

For North Elementary-please email Bethany at deweseb@pvo.k12.il.us.

For the Jr. High -please email Deb at FlesnerD@pvo.k12.il.us.

Please feel free to help pass the word to our PVO families!

Thank you. Mr. White.

Hi PVO Parents and Employees

The Governor has closed all school districts in the State of Illinois through March 30th. Therefore, at this time, the school will resume on March 31. There will be no practices allowed during this period of time for extra-curricular activities. Only employees are allowed in our schools during this time period. PVO Janitors will be doing a thorough cleaning during this time period too. Again, school will resume on March 31st.

Please stay healthy. Mr. White

post_text: The 8th-grade class participated in their first Socratic Seminar of the year. A Socratic Seminar is a discussion that is entirely student lead based on text. This discussion focused on three different poems related to the novel The Outsiders, which the class is currently reading. Each student was challenged to present a thought-provoking question, a response to a peer's question that was founded on text evidence, and also to contribute meaningful feedback to their peers! It was a great first seminar with several more to come! Awesome work 8th graders!

PVO earned 3 judge's choice awards at speech contests last month!

Brody, Aden, and Edward for their scripted performance "Franken Bro"
Alexis and Makennah for their scripted performance "The Raft"
Ellie, Lauren, Addi, and Miranda for their scripted performance "Wonder Wipes"

This award means they not only received a 1st place rating but also were THE BEST performance their contest judge saw the entire day of any school!! What a huge accomplishment!
